headlines.description: — In two days, Cam Thomas went from G League sensation to Brooklyn spark plug.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 27, Nets get lift from rookie to down Cavs

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored a season-high 32 points and hit his eighth three-pointer of the game with 12.9 seconds left as the Charlotte Hornets beat the Washington Wizards 109-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier's late 3-pointer helps Hornets over Wizards, 109-103

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 21 of his 30 points in the second half, Clint Capela finished with 10 points and 15 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks closed a perfect five-game homestand with a 113-101 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young takes control in 2nd half, Hawks beat Thunder 113-101

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 30 points, Jaylen Brown had 19 in his return from missing eight games with an injury and the Boston Celtics coasted by Houston 108-90 on Monday night, sending the Rockets to their 15th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Celtics send Rockets to 15th straight loss, 108-90

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored 21 points, Malcolm Brogdon added 16 more, and the Indiana Pacers routed the Chicago Bulls 109-77 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis, Brogdon pour it on in Pacers' 109-77 win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday scored 18 points and the Milwaukee Bucks opened the biggest halftime lead in franchise history on their way to a 123-92 blowout of the Orlando Magic on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks dominate Magic 123-92 for 4th consecutive victory

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 28 points and 10 rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves extended their winning streak to four with a 110-96 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns' 28 points paces Timberwolves past Pelicans, 110-96

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 23 points, Deandre Ayton had 21 points and 14 rebounds, and the Phoenix Suns beat the San Antonio Spurs 115-111 on Monday night for their 13th straight victory.
— After a 43-point loss to Minnesota a day earlier, Ja Morant and the Memphis Grizzlies had a 90-minute team meeting in Utah to clear the air.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's big finish helps Grizzlies edge Jazz, 119-118

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey had 24 points and the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers beat Sacramento 102-94 on Monday night, spoiling Alvin Gentry’s debut as interim Kings coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers pull away in 4th to beat Kings, spoil Gentry's debut
